##European football has become almost the antithesis of the global fight against the epidemic. What kind of dominoes will it push?

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

The integration of global sport is already very close. It is impossible to predict the ripple effect of the domino that European football has brought down in the world football world due to its obsession with profit and indecision.

Kevin | PHOENIX

Five major European Leagues have been shut down. What does this portend?

01

Europe has become the "Storm Center" of the overseas new championship epidemic, and the five major leagues and European football matches can not avoid being involved in the fate. Earlier this week, only Italy, La Liga and France, which are among the five major leagues that have been shut down, and the Premier League was set to continue this weekend, along with its own unusual approach to the disease The Bundesliga is also ready to play on weekends, but needs space.

However, the final struggles of the premier league and the Bundesliga have not been able to withstand the rapid spread of the epidemic among the clubs. Arsenal boss Mikel Arteta has been diagnosed with a new coronavirus, shortly after the Premier League announced it would resume play at the weekend, followed by Chelsea player John o'doyle. In addition, Leicester City, Bournemouth, Everton, Waterford and other teams have players with symptoms. The Premier League had to urgently revise its schedule, suspending all games on the evening of March 13, Beijing time, and resuming them no earlier than early April.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Premier League confirmed head coach Mikel Arteta (left) and player Edoy

Fußball-Bundesliga couldn't take it, either, and then announced a suspension of all weekend games. 2. Bundesliga's team Hanover 96 and Nuremberg have confirmed cases. The Bundesliga has decided to meet next Monday to discuss whether Fußball-Bundesliga and the Bundesliga will be suspended until early April.

So far, all five major European Leagues have been shut down. Other European soccer leagues, such as the Dutch League and the Portuguese Super League, have also been suspended, while UEFA has also declared the suspension of the Champions League and the UEFA League. Football in Europe has come to a complete standstill.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The five major leagues were shut down

This is definitely "see you later" ! The last time the top division was shut down was in 1939, with the outbreak of World War II.

In this storm in European football, only the Chinese, or those associated with China, seem to have foreseen it. The Chinese Super League team, Wuhan Jol, who is training there, has decided to return to China on Saturday, according to Spanish media reports. Wuhan drow coach González revealed the reason for returning home: "Now the Spanish epidemic is serious, China has basically no problem. "

Because of the domestic epidemic, the drow of Wuhan could not return to their base in Wuhan before and chose to go to Spain for training at the end of January. However, as the epidemic broke out in Spain, they had to turn back to their home country to "take refuge. " But returning to Wuhan is also unlikely, and must choose another city to stay.

The Wuhan decision was timely, as Reuters and other media reported on March 14 that the Spanish government had drafted a decree that would impose a nationwide blockade.

Chinese player Wu Lei, who is currently playing in La Liga, said on his personal wechat account: "The recent outbreak in Spain has also started to spread. The situation in the capital, Madrid, is relatively serious. I have received a lot of messages backstage from people who care about me and my family. Thank you very much. The world is fighting the virus, hope that domestic friends do not relax vigilance, do a good job of protection, to protect themselves and their families. We can all wait for a day of triumph!"

In addition, in a series of photos taken by foreign media on March 13 of Premier League Team Manchester United players arriving at the training ground, only the foreign aid Ihalo, who had joined on loan from Shanghai Shenhua, was wearing a mask, his strong sense of control and prevention is clearly tied to his experience in China.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
IHALO put on his mask

Recently, all walks of life in China have provided all-round assistance to Italy in combating the epidemic. "In terms of disease prevention, I would first like to thank China for helping Italy, which is really valuable, " said Charavy, who is training with Shanghai Shenhua in the United Arab Emirates

He also revealed that Shenhua teammates have decided to join him to continue to donate medical supplies to Italy. With the support of the Italian Consulate General in Shanghai, the supplies will soon be distributed to those most in need.

CHARAVY's compatriot Paillet of Shandong Luneng, who is also playing in the CSL, posted a picture of the Chinese medical team arriving in Italy on social media and "took off his hat" to express his thanks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshots of social media in Paillet

02

Although European football has finally been shut down, many people are asking: Why so late? Gary Neville, a former Manchester United Player and current Sky Sports commentator, said: "Premier League managers have made a mess of this by waiting until a club manager has been infected with a virus. Their behaviour is embarrassing. "

The reason why the professional leagues and UEFA are doing this is simple: money.

The sheer size of European football's economy forces managers to consider the impact on their financial interests in any decision they make. The Premier League, for example, has an economy that accounts for more than 1% of Britain's GDP, and taxes alone pay half the salaries of the country's police. The direct and indirect economic contribution of La Liga and the Segunda División League is also 1.37 per cent of Spanish GDP, almost 1.5 times that of the country's airline industry.

With the rapid development of commercialization, broadcasting rights and sponsorship fees are an important source of income for clubs and Professional Leagues. Once the Games are stopped, these revenues are wiped out. At the same time, the salaries of the players are still to be paid, if wages are suspended or reduced, the club is immediately defended by the players. At the moment in the major European Leagues, the cost of player salaries accounts for 50-80% of annual revenues, or even more than 100% in a single season; for some of the big clubs, total salaries of $200m-$300m a year have become the norm. If the suspension time is too long, some clubs appear the financial chain fracture, finally bankrupt the possibility is very big.

According to this logic, the major European leagues will do everything possible to avoid suspension, first of all, allowing the game to continue while the epidemic is already spreading; if it gets worse, playing on an empty field, that would preserve revenue in the broadcast and sponsorship sectors, which are higher than live ticket sales; the shutdown would only be announced if it proved too much to bear.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
An aerial view shows an empty field during the Serie A derby between CLUBE ATLÉTICO Juventus and Inter Milan on March 8 | Xinhua

Look at Serie A, the first of the five major leagues to shut down: Before the Italian government mandated a national stadium to be empty, many smaller clubs were still opposing empty stadiums at league meetings, because ticket revenue is also very important to them. Even at the "critical moment" when there were nearly, confirmed cases of NCP in the country, the decision to shut down Serie A came from the government, not professional leagues and clubs.

Moreover, the current "lockout" is announced to extend, not to cancel completely, because if the season write-off, the league's direct losses will reach hundreds of millions, billions of euros scale, which the clubs simply can not afford. So, even if most of the next game is going to be open, it's going to have to be played through.

The same is true for UEFA. It has been slow to announce a postponement of this year's European Cup, even after the owner of Greece's Olympiakos team was diagnosed with new pneumonia, despite an application by the Premier League's wolves for an extension, insisted that the latter go to Greece on schedule to play both teams in the Europa League. It's all about maximizing economic returns.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
UEFA has been slow to announce whether Euro 2020 will be postponed

But it's not an honorable thing to do. In the face of life, sports should undoubtedly take second place, not to mention attached to the economic interests of sports. European football, which used to set an example for the world, has become the antithesis.

03

Although UEFA will not meet until next week to decide whether this year's European Cup will be postponed, this is a highly probable event. At present, the suspension of major European Leagues Until early April is clearly only a "delaying tactic. " In view of the current epidemic situation in various countries, until June, when the European Cup is scheduled to be held, whether the players can play normally, it requires a huge question mark. In particular, this year's Euro 2010, which celebrates the 60th anniversary of the tournament, for the first time has chosen to be held in 12 cities in 11 countries and across Europe without a host country, it's very difficult to predict that the entire area will be secure before the event can proceed as planned.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For Euro 2020

In addition, after the epidemic has passed, the first priority of the National Leagues must be to resume their operations, it is not possible to play the European Cup First; the original schedule of the European Cup to make up for the previous delay in the League is the most practical. At the same time, UEFA's own Champions League and UEFA's own Champions League will take time to make up for. Taken together, the biggest sound so far is "Euro 2012 postponed for a year, 2021" .

But it's not that simple. 2021, the year FIFA held its long planned inaugural club New World Cup, has decided to hold it in China. If the World Club Cup and the European Cup crash, then many European clubs may only send their second-line players, youth players to participate in the World Club Cup, FIFA can not tolerate this situation. In fact, the New World Club Cup is FIFA's weapon against UEFA's Champions League. How can the two give in so easily?

Hosting the club World Cup would have been very good for Chinese football, but if it conflicts with the European Cup, the interests of all parties will no doubt be damaged. What if the 2021 club World Cup is postponed? And it's hard. If the club World Cup is postponed to 2022, it will be the same year's World Cup, although Qatar hosted the World Cup in the winter, but the summer club World Cup in the winter to play the World Cup, players are exhausted, certainly will not agree. Another year to the 2023? China to host Asian Cup

The renovation of the Shanghai Stadium, one of the stadiums hosting the 2021, has been officially restored, March 10,2020
